        <Parent_String>market centers (inhabited places) [300387285], settlements by economic base [300120583], inhabited places [300008347], Settlements and Landscapes (hierarchy name) [300008346], Built Environment (hierarchy name) [300264550], Objects Facet [300264092]</Parent_String>
        <Hier_Rel_Type>Genus/Species-BTG</Hier_Rel_Type>
      </Preferred_Parent>
    </Parent_Relationships>
    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Communities of relatively small size that hold a market, typically agricultural centers in a rural area. Market towns typically developed as a location to trade farm products, sometimes near fortified places.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000114707/Oxford English Dictionary Online (2002-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Relativ kleine Gemeinde, die einen Markt zum Handeln landwirtschaftlicher Produkte veranstaltet, typischerweise ein landwirtschaftliches Zentrum in einer ländlichen Region. Zuweilen befand sie sich in der Nähe einer Befestigungsanlage.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>German</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000232/IfM-SMB-PK</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000122134/IfM Berlin</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>內有市集的相對小型社區，一般為鄉村地區的為農業中心。市集城鎮通常發展為交易農產品的地點，有時在防禦要塞附近。

</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
